That's what I thought, but I didn't spot a CBM port on the PMA in any of BobCat's pictures, so I asked.
Do you have to send it with a spacecraft piece by piece, or is it just done already?

Do you have to send it with a spacecraft piece by piece, or is it just done already?

There is a pre-built craft version, but the only way to get it into space is to hack it there. Otherwise, yes, you have to build it piece by piece, just like the real astronauts did.

Sending it piece by piece is more fun I think, but im just afraid im sending the wrong parts into the space.

And how to hack it there then?

Sending it piece by piece is more fun I think, but im just afraid im sending the wrong parts into the space.

And how to hack it there then?

Use a mod like Hyperedit, or the warp-to-orbit function on the magic ORDA computer, if you have that. And there are all sorts of places on the web to find in what order the parts were sent up and how they were sent up (use the Buran as opposed to the NASA shuttle). Use this as an excuse to learn all about the ISS, how they dock it together (PMA or CBM), and all the rest of the really interesting stuff that goes on up there.

The issue was trying to have 2 docking ports. that was the issue. It is very possible that nothing was "wrong" with the file, but that trying to have 2 docking ports on the same part, caused Unity/KSP to choke.

the issue was solved by making it a 'one' port part. requiring a CBM on the other side.
